population: Recipient Population (a-b)/b recipient_trade_world:Recipient Total Trade with World gdp_per_growth: GDP per capita growth (a-b)/b GDP_total_growth: GDP total growth

First, let’s visualize the distribution of the missing data.

vis_miss(aid)

vis_miss(aid,cluster = TRUE)

we decide to drop the observations that have missing values for the following reason: 1. “MNAR: Missing Not at Random - the missing is not random, it correlates with unobservable characteristics unknown to a researcher.” 2. we still have 80% data left.

aid = aid %>%
  na.omit(aid)
